    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-19T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-19T11:00:00-05:00" n="898"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d898">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EW/1–1945: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-19T19:00:00+03:00"
                            >January 19, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 19—4:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>183. Meeting with the Hungarians took place today as scheduled. The Hungarian
                    delegation questioned the interpretation of various of the articles but no
                    changes were made in the text of the document. It was agreed that the armistice
                    would be signed tomorrow at 3:30 p.m. Moscow time.</p>
                <p>I understand that a general statement will be made over the Soviet radio tomorrow
                    night, Saturday, at 7 p.m. and we have agreed that the text of the armistice
                    will be released simultaneously in the three capitals at 7 p.m. Sunday Moscow
                    time.</p>
                <p>A few very minor last minute changes in wording will be wired by the British
                    Embassy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
